# lemniscate

- _lemniscate(a=1)_

The lemniscate, also called the lemniscate of Bernoulli.
Defined as the locus of points such that the product of distances from two fixed points _(-a,0)_ and _(a,0)_ is a constant _a^2_.

~~~spl svg=A
(0 -- 2.pi).functionPlot(
	lemniscate(1)
)
~~~

